          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>No Government No Pay Act of 2015</b></p> <p> A Member of Congress may not receive pay, during a government shutdown, equal to the product of 1 day's worth of pay under such annual rate and the number of 24-hour periods during which the government shutdown is in effect. This prohibition is applicable to days occurring during the 114th and succeeding Congresses.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
